article.description: — Dhashon Dyson's 19 points helped Bethune-Cookman defeat Alabama State 79-68 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Dyson scores 19 in Bethune-Cookman's 79-68 win over Alabama State
article.linkText: Dyson scores 19 in Bethune-Cookman's 79-68 win over Alabama State
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- — Dhashon Dyson's 19 points helped Bethune-Cookman defeat Alabama State 79-68 on Saturday night. Dyson added six rebounds for the Wildcats (10-11, 5-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Zion Harmon scored 16 points and added three steals. Reggie Ward Jr. had 14 points and shot 4 of 10 from the field and 6 for 6 from the line. The Hornets (10-11, 5-3) were led by Antonio Madlock with 17 points and four steals. CJ Hines had 12 points and Amarr Knox finished scored 11. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
